record_data.record_plain_text: 1. Availability: Seller makes electric energy, capacity and ancillary services available as a power marketer under this Tariff for wholesale sales to any purchaser with whom Seller has contracted. 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy, capacity and ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of Seller. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at the rates established between Seller and the purchaser. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 5. Ancillary Services: Seller will make available to any purchaser with whom it has contracted, the ancillary services listed in this Paragraph. a. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. b. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include l0-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, l0-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. c. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. d. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. e. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. f Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. ("SPP") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. g. Third-Party Ancillary Services: Seller Offers Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 7. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Southwest region and a Category 1 seller in the Northeast, Southeast, Central, Southwest Power Pool, and Northwest regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). 8. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16. Seller has also received waiver of: Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141 with the exception of 18 C.F.R. 141.14 and 141.15. Seller has also received blanket approval under Part 34. (See Pacific Wind Lessee, LLC, Docket No. ER12-1931-000, (July 3, 2012) (unpublished letter order)). 9. Effective Date: This Tariff is effective on the date specified by the Commission.

ARTICLE 2 CONSTRUCTION, JOINT OWNERSHIP AND USE OF SHARED FACILITIES; SECURING LAND RIGHTS OVER TRANSMISSION ROUTE 2.1 Construction of Shared Facilities The First Mover with respect to any applicable Segment of the Gen-tie Line shall have the right to construct the Shared Facilities located in that Segment. The other Parties whose Projects will require an ownership interest in an applicable Segment of the Gen-Tie Line shall be Second Movers in respect of such applicable Segment. Each Owner that is a Second Mover in respect of an applicable Segment shall have the right to provide written no tice to the First Mover of its desire to become the First Mover with respect to such Segment. If a Second Mover in respect of an applicable Segment provides such notice to the First Mover in respect of such applicable Segment, the First Mover will either (1) reasonably demonstrate to such Second Mover that it is working expeditiously and is in a position to construct the applicable Segment of the Shared Facilities as quickly as such Second Mover could construct the applicable Segment of the Shared Facilities (in which case the Owner that is the First Mover in respect of such applicable Segment will continue to be the First Mover in respect of such applicable Segment), or (2) acknowledge in writing that the Owner that was previously a Second Mover in respect of such applicable Segment shall be prospectively considered the First Mover in respect of such applicable Segment and the Owner that was previously the First Mover in respect of such applicable Segment shall be prospectively considered a Second Mover in respect of such applicable Segment. Any disputes that arise in relation to the party that is considered the First Mover in respect of an applicable Segment shall be resolved in accordance with Section 10. The First Mover shall reasonably cooperate with a Second Mover with respect to the assignment of any and all contracts entered into by the First Mover related to one or more Segments of the Shared Facilities to a Second Mover, including contracts related to design, procurement, construction, of the Shared Facilities, to the extent a Second Mover is prospectively considered the First Mover in respect of an applicable Segment pursuant to this Section 2.1. The First Mover shall cause the Shared Facilities to be constructed in a good and workmanlike manner, and in accordance with all Applicable Laws, Permits and applicable real property rights and shall use commercially reasonable efforts to complete such construction in time to meet the earliest backfeed requirement date of the Projects utilizing the applicable Segments under construction. The Shared Facilities upon completion of construction shall be owned by the Parties free and clear of all liens (other than Permitted Liens). Costs related to the construction of the Shared Facilities shall be shared by the Parties as described in Section 4.4 below. 2.2 Joint Ownership and Use of Shared Facilities Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the ownership and use of the Shared Facilities shall be as follows: (a) The First Mover in respect of an applicable Segment, concurrent with the Shared Facilities Construction Payment Date for an applicable Second Mover, shall grant, sell, assign and convey to such Second Mover in respect of an applicable Segment (and its successors and assigns) an undivided tenancy-in-common interest in the applicable Segment equal to each such Second Mover's Proportionate Share of the Segment. The foregoing assignment shall occur automatically and concurrently with the vesting of title in the First Mover to one or more Segments of the Shared Facilities (including the equipment and services related thereto) (as they may be added and as they otherwise may exist from time to time). Each Owner that makes the Shared Facilities Construction Payment will hold its ownership interest in the applicable Segments of the Shared Facilities as a tenant-in-common. The ownership structure set forth in this Section 2.2 is not organized with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making a profit from the operation of the Shared Facilities or any Segment thereof, but merely as an ownership form through which the Owners can accomplish their joint purpose of owning, operating and making the Shared Facilities available for the use of the Owners in connection with their respective Projects or other renewable energy projects developed by the Parties. At no time shall the Shared Facilities or any Segment thereof be used by any person other than an applicable Owner or such Owner's assignees, licensees and permittees. Subject to the rights of each Owner under Article 8 in the event of the possible sale or other disposition of its ownership interest in the Shared Facilities, or under Section 13.5 in the event all or a portion of the Shared Facilities is or are removed from service, the Owners do not expect to receive any material amount of revenue from the Shared Facilities. For the avoidance of doubt, (i) the Fiberoptic Communication Lines will not be part of the Shared Facilities, and each Party shall separately own and be responsible for all costs and the operation and maintenance of the Fiberoptic Communication Lines identified on Exhibit B hereto which are indicated as being owned by such Party, and (ii) certain portions of Rose Meadow will not be part of the Shared Facilities, and the applicable Party shall separately own and be responsible for all costs and the operation and maintenance of the portions of Rose Meadow identified on Exhibit C hereto which are indicated as being owned by such Party. (b) Each Owner shall at all times, and at its sole cost and expense, maintain in good working order and repair, in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices and the Settlement Agreement, each part of its Project which, if not maintained in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice and the Settlement Agreement, could reasonably be expected to adversely affect, in a material way, the Shared Facilities. In the event an Owner fails to so maintain its Project, which failure, in the reasonable judgment of any Owner or the Shared Facilities Manager, does or is reasonably likely to adversely affect, in a material way, the Shared Facilities, any such party may, at its option, notify the defaulting Owner, and the defaulting Owner shall have the obligation to promptly cure such failure to maintain such portion of such Owner's Project, provided the notifying party has given at least five (5) Business Days' advance notice to the defaulting Owner in order for such defaulting Owner to cure any failure. Notwithstanding the foregoing, no such notice and opportunity to cure shall be required if such failure poses actual or imminent risk of serious personal injury or material physical damage to the Shared Facilities requiring immediate preventative or remedial action, as determined in good faith by any Owner or the Shared Facilities Manager. Any Project disconnected may be reconnected when the part of such Owner's Project, the failure of which to maintain in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice or the Settlement Agreement was the cause of the disconnection, is remedied and brought into compliance with Prudent Industry Practice or the Settlement Agreement as determined in the reasonable discretion of the other Owners. (c) Each Owner shall promptly take such action (including, but not limited to, the execution, acknowledgment, delivery and recordation of separate deeds, assignments, bills of sale, and other documents and instruments) as may reasonably be requested by any other Owner to effect, evidence or vest each Owner's respective ownership interest in the Shared Facilities or any Segment thereof, or to evidence the transfer by such other Owner of any of its ownership interest in the Shared Facilities or any Segment thereof. 2.3 Securing Land Rights Over Transmission Route The Parties acknowledge that stand alone easements ("Easements"), deeds, leases, licenses and other real property agreements ("Real Property Rights") should be obtained for the Shared Facilities over and across the Transmission Route. Any internal overhead costs incurred by a Second Mover in relation to obtaining the Real Property Rights including travel costs related thereto, shall be paid by such Second Mover. Notwithstanding any provision of the Real Property Rights that would allow termination of such Real Property Rights, each Owner shall keep and maintain such Real Property Rights in full force and effect for so long as this Agreement is in force and effect. The defaulting Owner shall, upon demand, reimburse the non-defaulting Owner for all reasonable and verifiable out-of-pocket costs, fees and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees and expenses) incurred by the non-defaulting Owner in curing any such default by the defaulting Owner under the Real Property Rights. Upon receipt by any Owner of a notice of default under the Real Property Rights, the Owner receiving such notice shall immediately deliver a copy thereof to the other Owner and any Lender. 2.4 Obtaining Permits and Approvals for Shared Facilities; Design and Cost Estimates for Shared Facilities First Mover for the applicable Segment(s) shall be the lead Party and shall use commercially reasonable efforts, with the reasonable cooperation of the Second Movers, to cause the County to subject the Shared Facilities to environmental review under the California Environmental Quality Act (CEQA, Code section 21000, et. seq.) and obtain all necessary Permits for the First Mover for the applicable Segment(s) to construct the Shared Facilities related to the applicable Segment(s) for the benefit of the Owners in accordance with this Agreement. ARTICLE 3 OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES 3.1 Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities From and after the Interconnection Date for each Interconnected Project, each Owner of an Interconnected Project shall pay its Proportionate Interconnected Share of all future costs of operating and maintaining the applicable Segment(s) of the Shared Facilities utilized by such Interconnected Project in accordance herewith, as such costs are established and approved by the Owners Committee, subject to each Owner's rights of approval and disapproval as set forth in Article 4. 3.2 Removal of Property Each Owner shall have the express right, at any time and in its sole discretion, to remove and/or replace any part of its Project and all other property owned by such Owner, to the extent not jointly owned by the Owners. If removal or replacement of any of such property will materially affect in an adverse way the safety or operation of any of the Shared Facilities, the Owner contemplating the removal or replacement shall consult with and obtain the consent of the other Owner(s) before conducting the contemplated removal or replacement, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. 3.3 Line Losses Any line losses occurring between an Interconnected Project's substation and Whirlwind that cannot be specifically allocated to the operation of one Interconnected Project (i.e., as when there is only one Interconnected Project) shall be allocated to the Owners of Interconnected Projects so that any and all incremental line losses caused by a subsequent Interconnected Project over and above those resulting from the operation of any other prior Interconnected Project shall be allocated to such subsequent Interconnected Project. For the avoidance of doubt, such allocation of line losses shall reflect the incremental contribution of losses caused by the injection of electric current from a subsequent Interconnected Project, where line losses are proportional to the square of the electric currents injected by the Interconnected Projects, multiplied by the conductor and transformer resistance of the line. Automated equipment capable of measuring and recording the line losses attributable to each Interconnected Project shall be installed and maintained as part of the Shared Facilities. The Owners of Interconnected Projects shall reasonably cooperate with each other as necessary in the calculation of line losses set forth in this Section and each Interconnected Project will be responsible for the costs and installation of meters at its Interconnected Project to give effect to the foregoing calculation of line losses. ARTICLE 4 SHARED FACILITIES MANAGEMENT 4.1 Shared Facilities Manager (a) EAH shall be the initial "Shared Facilities Manager," subject to its right to resign as Shared Facilities Manager upon one hundred eighty (180) calendar days' notice to the Owners. If EAH (or any other entity) resigns as Shared Facilities Manager, the successor Shared Facilities Manager shall be selected by the Owners Committee. In addition, any Owner may unilaterally remove any Shared Facilities Manager for (i) such Shared Facilities Manager's material failure to comply with its obligations (under this Agreement or a separate shared facilities management agreement, as applicable) within five (5) Business Days' notice and opportunity to cure (plus, in the case of a non-monetary default, such additional time as may be reasonably necessary provided cure is commenced within such five (5)-Business Day period and diligently and continuously prosecuted to completion), (ii) the Bankruptcy of Shared Facilities Manager, or (iii) a sale, assignment, transfer or other disposition of its interest in the Shared Facilities or this Agreement that is not in accordance with the provisions of Article 8. If a Shared Facilities Manager is removed pursuant to this Section 4.1(a), the successor Shared Facilities Manager shall be selected by the Owners Committee. (b) The Shared Facilities Manager shall serve for a term of twenty (20) years. No later than one hundred eighty (180) calendar days prior to the end of such term, the Owners Committee shall agree on the Shared Facilities Manager for the next succeeding term. If the Shared Facilities Manager is a third party, such party shall provide services pursuant to a contract satisfactory to the Owners Committee and consistent with (but not limited to) the requirements that would be applicable to the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to this Agreement if the Shared Facilities Manager were one of the Owners. The foregoing shall apply with respect to each successive twenty (20) year period until this Agreement is terminated. 4.2 Powers and Duties of Shared Facilities Manager The Shared Facilities Manager shall be authorized and obligated to do the following on behalf of each of the Owners; provided, however, that the Shared Facilities Manager shall not be bound by a fiduciary duty to such Owners: (a) Operate and maintain the Shared Facilities in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice, Applicable Laws, the Settlement Agreement and applicable interconnection agreements to which any Owner is a party, and commercially reasonable terms included in any insurance policies covering the Shared Facilities of which the Shared Facilities Manager has received notice. The Shared Facilities Manager either directly or through one or more subcontractors will provide for the operations and maintenance of the Shared Facilities, including procurement of spare parts and such other services as may be desirable consistent with Prudent Industry Practice, the Settlement Agreement and Applicable Laws. In connection with any scheduled operation and maintenance, upon reasonable notice to the Owner(s) affected, the Shared Facilities Manager is authorized to require each Owner, upon no less than five (5) Business Days' notice, to disconnect all or any portions of its Project, in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice, the Settlement Agreement and in compliance with the terms of this Agreement. The Shared Facilities Manager shall coordinate with the Owner(s) affected to schedule the interruption, to the extent possible consistent with the standards set forth above, at a time least likely to adversely affect such Owners' projects, and to minimize the length of the interruption. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Shared Facilities Manager shall operate and maintain the Shared Facilities in a non-discriminatory manner, treating each Owner and its Project equally and fairly. Without limiting the foregoing, in the event the California Independent System Operator notifies the Shared Facilities Manager of any curtailment of interconnection service and directs the Shared Facilities Manager to implement such curtailment with respect to all of the Interconnected Projects (as opposed to the California Independent System Operator notifying one or more Owner(s) of any curtailment of interconnection service pursuant to such Owner(s) generator interconnection agreement or equivalent), such curtailment shall be allocated by the Shared Facilities Manager on a pro rata basis based upon the Proportionate Interconnected Share of the Owners, except when such pro rata allocations would be in violation of the applicable curtailment instruction, and such persons will be responsible for all costs, liabilities, and damages relating to such curtailment. In the event the Transmission Provider notifies the Shared Facilities Manager of any curtailment by Transmission Provider (including at the direction of Transmission Provider when the basis of such curtailment is congestion arising from the ordinary course of operations of Transmission Provider's transmission system) and directs the Shared Facilities Manager to implement such curtailment with respect to all of the Interconnected Projects (as opposed to the Transmission Provider notifying one or more Owner(s) of any curtailment pursuant to such Owner(s) generator interconnection agreement or equivalent), such curtailment shall be allocated by the Shared Facilities Manager on a pro rata basis based upon the Proportionate Interconnected Share of the Owners, except when such pro rata allocations would be in violation of the applicable curtailment instruction, and such persons will be responsible for all costs, liabilities, and damages relating to such curtailment. (b) Prepare annual budgets and budget amendments as required with respect to the Shared Facilities and present such budgets and budget amendments for review and approval by the Owners Committee (in the case of each annual budget, by no later than October 1 of the year prior to the year to which the budget relates); (c) Maintain books and records related to the Shared Facilities in accordance with generally acceptable accounting principles and international financial reporting standards (as adopted by the International Accounting Standards Board from time to time) applicable to the electric utility industry and make such books and records available to each of the Owners upon the request of such Owner during the Shared Facilities Manager's regular business hours; (d) Procure policies of insurance in accordance with Section 7.1; (e) Perform, in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice and the Settlement Agreement, such other duties as may be specified by the Owners Committee and agreed to by the Shared Facilities Manager; (f) Execute such contracts and other documents as are necessary or appropriate to carry out the duties enumerated in Sections 4.2(a) through 4.2(e); (g) Serve as an additional notice party with respect to the retail electricity bills for each Owner, and if any Owner shall fail to pay such bills five (5) Business Days prior to the due date thereof, then pay such bills prior to such due date for any Owner (regardless of whether funds are paid to the Shared Facilities Manager by the Owners in accordance with such invoices, pursuant to Section 4.4 or otherwise), and promptly pay (to the extent of funds paid to the Shared Facilities Manager by the Owners pursuant to Section 4.4 or otherwise) all other bills and charges of third parties related to or in connection with the carrying out of the duties and obligations of the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to this Agreement; (h) Upon the request of any Owner, promptly provide to such Owner a statement, in such detail as may be reasonably requested by such Owner, of the amounts paid or payable or reimbursed or reimbursable by such Owner pursuant to Section 4.4; (i) Notify each Owner of (i) the assertion of any claim for bodily injury or property damage in excess of Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000) or greater related to the Shared Facilities promptly following the Shared Facilities Manager's knowledge of any such assertion and (ii) the Shared Facilities Manager's knowledge of the occurrence of an event likely, in the reasonable determination of the Shared Facilities Manager, to result in the assertion of such a claim promptly following any such occurrence. If any loss, damage or impairment to the Shared Facilities occurs, the Shared Facilities Manager shall apply the proceeds of any insurance policy with respect thereto to repair, replace or restore the Shared Facilities to their prior condition if and to the extent permitted or required pursuant to the provisions of this Agreement; (j) Prepare, submit to each Owner for review and comment, and file in a timely manner any and all property tax returns required to be filed with respect to the Shared Facilities; and include in budgets submitted to the Owners and pay in a timely manner any property tax owed in connection therewith, taking advantage of all available discounts for early payment (it being agreed, however, that each Owner shall have the right to protest any property tax assessment against the Shared Facilities, and shall be entitled to recoup its costs in such contest to the extent they can be recouped out of tax savings achieved, whether in a single year or series of years); and (k) Except as permitted by this Agreement, the Shared Facilities Manager shall not assign, subcontract or otherwise delegate its obligations hereunder other than to an Affiliate thereof without the consent of the Owners Committee. 4.3 Authorized Expenditures To the extent included in an annual budget or a budget amendment approved and effective pursuant to Sections 5.7 through 5.9 of this Agreement, from and after the Interconnection Date for each Interconnected Project on an applicable Segment of the Shared Facilities, each of the Owners of such Interconnected Projects for such Segment shall reimburse to the Shared Facilities Manager its Proportionate Interconnected Share of (i) the salaries, wages and related indirect and reasonable overhead costs to the extent directly allocable to the applicable Segment of the Shared Facilities for the Shared Facilities Manager's personnel who perform the duties and obligations of the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to this Agreement and (ii) the reasonable payments by the Shared Facilities Manager to third parties related to or in connection with the carrying out of the duties and obligations of the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to this Agreement. Each Owner shall pay to the Shared Facilities Manager any amount undisputed by such Owner set forth in such statement within ten (10) Business Days. (c) Notwithstanding the provisions of Sections 4.4(a) and 4.4(b) above, the Shared Facilities Manager shall make available during regular business hours, for inspection and audit by each of the Owners of an applicable Segment, all books and records of the Shared Facilities Manager evidencing the amounts contained in each statement and accounting provided to such Owner pursuant to Sections 4.4(a) and 4.4(b). Such books and records shall be retained by the Shared Facilities Manager for such period as the Owners Committee may determine, but not less than one (1) year; and such books and records shall be made available by the Shared Facilities Manager for inspection and audit by each of the Owners during the Shared Facilities Manager's regular business hours. The costs and expenses of any inspection or audit requested by an Owner shall be borne by the Owner requesting such inspection or audit. (d) The Shared Facilities Manager also shall permit any Owner to inspect the Shared Facilities during regular business hours, provided that such Owner provides at least one Business Day's notice of such inspection and complies with the safety requirements imposed by the Shared Facilities Manager on all visitors. ARTICLE 5 OWNERS COMMITTEE 5.1 Establishment of Committee; Voting There is hereby established an "Owners Committee" for the Owners of Interconnected Projects to take all actions with respect to the Segments which have not been delegated to the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to Article 4, except as otherwise provided in Section 5.8, and to take all other actions that all of the Owners of Interconnected Projects for one or more applicable Segments may, from time to time, agree in writing that the Owners Committee is authorized to take in connection with the ownership (as applicable), construction, rebuilding, operation, maintenance, repair, replacement and removal of the Segments, or any portion thereof. There shall be up to nine (9) classes of Owners of Interconnected Projects (individually, a "Class", and collectively, the "Classes") for purposes of membership on the Owners Committee: Class A (AW and its successors and transferees), Class B (AW2 and its successors and transferees), Class C (VS and its successors and transferees), Class D (CS and its successors and transferees), Class E (PW and its successors and transferees), Class F (PW2 and its successors and transferees), Class G (EDC and its successors and transferees), Class H (CS2 and its successors and transferees), and Class I (BAR13 and its successors and transferees). Each member of the Owners Committee representing a Class shall be entitled to cast the number of votes equal to the Maximum Interconnection Capacity for the applicable Owner's Interconnected Project. Each member of the Owners Committee representing a Class shall have the right to cast such vote with respect to any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners Committee in respect of one or more Segments in which each Owner represented by a Class is an Owner. If an Owners Committee member representing a Class is entitled to vote on the matter presented to the Owners Committee and is participating in a meeting of the Owners Committee but does not vote either in favor of or against any matter subject to a decision, approval or other action of the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement, such member shall be deemed to have voted against. A matter shall be deemed approved by the Owners Committee only if it shall have been approved by a majority of the votes of the members of the Owners Committee representing a Class entitled to vote on the matter presented to the Owners Committee and in attendance at the meeting. 5.2 Appointment of Members; Alternates The initial number of members of the Owners Committee shall be one (1) representing Class E. Each Owner of an Interconnected Project, at any time following such Owner's Project becoming an Interconnected Project, shall be entitled to appoint one (1) member to the Owners Committee representing its Class, which appointment shall be deemed effective upon notice to the other Owners. Any Owner of an Interconnected Project (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively) may change its Owners Committee member(s) (and the total number of Owners Committee members in its Class) by giving notice of such changes to each other Owner. Any Owner of an Interconnected Project (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively), by giving notice to each other Owners, may, for purposes of any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement, appoint an alternate or alternates to serve on the Owners Committee in the place of, and to cast the vote of, the regular Owners Committee member appointed by such Owner of an Interconnected Project. 5.3 Meetings The Owners Committee shall meet at such time and place as may be agreed upon by the members of the Owners Committee representing a Class entitled to vote on the matter to be presented to the Owners Committee, and the Owners Committee shall meet at such other times and places as may be requested by any Owners Committee member by notice to each other Owners Committee member at least ten (10) calendar days prior to such meeting. Members of the Owners Committee may participate in such meetings in person or by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications during which all persons participating in the meeting can hear each other. Participation in a meeting by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications shall be deemed to constitute presence in person at the meeting. No actions or decisions of the Owners Committee may be taken or made at any meeting without a quorum being present. A quorum shall be convened if Owners Committee members representing at least seventy-five percent (75%) of the aggregate votes eligible to be cast on a matter are in attendance at any properly called meeting of the Owners Committee. 5.4 Decisions by Written Action Any decisions, approvals and other actions that may be taken at a meeting of the Owners Committee may be taken without a meeting if all Owners Committee members representing a Class entitled to vote on the matter presented to the Owners Committee consent thereto in writing. The Owners Committee may, by the unanimous vote of the members of the Owners Committee representing a Class entitled to vote on the matter presented to the Owners Committee, adopt procedures for review or approval of matters or for the taking of other actions concerning the Segments. 5.5 Subcommittees The Owners Committee may appoint such subcommittees as it deems necessary or appropriate and, by the unanimous vote of all of the members of the Owners Committee representing a Class entitled to vote on the matter presented to the Owners Committee, may delegate approval authority to such subcommittees with respect to matters concerning the Segments. Members of a subcommittee are not required to otherwise be a member of the Owners Committee. 5.6 Major Decisions Notwithstanding anything in the Agreement to the contrary, the following shall require the unanimous approval of all members of the Owners Committee: (a) approval or amendment of the annual budgets and budget amendments prepared by the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to Section 4.2(b); (b) approval of contracts or commitments involving or expected to involve aggregate expenditures of more than $100,000.00 for expenses within a budget approved by the Owners Committee (or otherwise in effect pursuant to Section 5.7); (c) approval of the incurrence of costs, with respect to any line item in a budget approved by the Owners Committee (or otherwise in effect pursuant to Section 5.7) in excess of 150% of such line item budget; (d) approval of incurrent of aggregate costs for any calendar year in excess of 125% of the total budgeted costs for such year as set forth in a budget approved by the Owners Committee (or otherwise in effect pursuant to Section 5.7); (e) any decision to remove from service permanently or otherwise to sell, transfer, assign or dispose (other than as may be permitted pursuant to Article 8) of all or any part of the Shared Facilities; and (f) any decision to incur or to authorize the Shared Facilities Manager to incur any indebtedness related to the Shared Facilities that the Owners would be obligated to repay pursuant to this Agreement. 5.7 Budgets If for any reason the Owners Committee does not approve an annual budget prior to the end of the eleventh (11th) month of the preceding calendar year (other than the budget applicable during the year in which the first Shared Facilities are constructed), the budget for such preceding year shall apply to the current year, subject to an increase or decrease in such budget to reflect the change in the gross domestic product implicit price deflator ("GDPIPD") as defined by the U.S. Department of Commerce (or appropriate replacement index should the GDPIPD be discontinued) for all goods and services during the twelve (12)-month period ending with the tenth (10th) month of such preceding year. 5.8 Emergency Actions The Shared Facilities Manager (or any Owner of an Interconnected Project, if Shared Facilities Manager is unavailable or fails to act) shall have the right but not the duty to proceed with an item that has not been approved (even if it has been disapproved) as provided in this Article 5, if the Shared Facilities Manager (or any Owner of an Interconnected Project, if Shared Facilities Manager is unavailable or fails to act) determines in its reasonable judgment that such action is required to avoid an imminent threat of loss of life or property or is required to avoid an imminent threat of interruption of service to the acting Owner of an Interconnected Project; provided, however, that Shared Facilities Manager (or any Owner of an Interconnected Project, if Shared Facilities Manager is unavailable or fails to act) must give notice of such action to each Owner of an Interconnected Project as soon as reasonably possible and further provided that if the Shared Facilities Manager (or any Owner of an Interconnected Project) takes such action on a disapproved item and if the determination made in any subsequent review of the decision is that the item was not consistent with Prudent Industry Practice or the Settlement Agreement, then the Shared Facilities Manager (or such Owner of an Interconnected Project) shall not be entitled to reimbursement for any of the cost or expense of such action. 5.9 Tax Election Each of the Owners shall, to the extent permitted by Section 761 of the Code, elect as provided in Treasury Regulation Section 1.761-2 to exclude from the provisions of Subchapter K of the Code any organization that they may otherwise comprise by virtue of this Agreement. 5.10 Deadlocks If the Owners Committee reaches deadlock on an issue (a "Deadlock"), and any Party gives written notice to the other(s) that such has occurred, then the Owners of Interconnected Projects will use all reasonable efforts to reach a satisfactory solution by referring the Deadlock to senior management of each of the Owners of Interconnected Projects or their parent entities. In the event that a Deadlock has been declared, senior management of the Owners of Interconnected Projects or their parent entities will meet as soon as possible, on no less than five (5) Business Days' notice, unless specifically agreed otherwise. 5.11 Deadlocks Beyond Senior Management Negotiations Such senior management shall examine any submissions by the Owners of the Interconnected Projects, and shall, if the Deadlock cannot be resolved immediately, agree to convene for further negotiations aimed at resolving the Deadlock. In the case of technical or operational issues, should such senior management be unable to resolve the Deadlock within thirty (30) calendar days from the notice of Deadlock, any Owner of an Interconnected Project may deliver a notice to the other Owners of Interconnected Projects certifying that despite such Owner's good faith efforts to resolve the Deadlock, a Deadlock persists, whereupon the matter shall be resolved by the determination of a mutually agreed, independent consultant with experience in the windpower industry ("Consultant"), and each Owner of Interconnected Projects shall cooperate in facilitating a decision by the Consultant. If in the opinion of the Consultant the resolution is substantially in accord with the position of one Owner of an Interconnected Project, the other Owners of Interconnected Projects shall bear the cost of the Consultant; otherwise, the Owners of Interconnected Projects shall bear such cost in accordance with their respective Proportionate Interconnected Shares. In the case of non-technical or non-operational issues, any Deadlock that cannot be resolved by further negotiations by such senior management pursuant to the Section 5.11 shall be determined as set forth in Article 10. The Parties acknowledge that time is of the essence in completing the Shared Facilities. Therefore, in the event of a dispute that is not resolved in thirty (30) calendar days, First Mover shall have the right to move forward with preliminary design, final design, and procurement and construction of the Shared Facilities consistent with the requirements set forth in this Agreement. Costs incurred by First Mover during the period of the dispute shall be paid initially by First Mover but shall be apportioned between the Parties as part of the dispute resolution. ARTICLE 6 COVENANTS 6.1 Covenants of the Owners The Owners hereby covenant as follows: (a) Mechanic's Liens. Each Owner shall not permit any mechanic's liens arising out of its use of the Shared Facilities pursuant to this Agreement to exist against the Shared Facilities. If an Owner wishes to contest any such lien, that Owner shall, within sixty (60) calendar days after it receives notice of the lien, provide a bond or other security to the other Owners as those other Owners may reasonably request, or remove such lien from the affected property pursuant to Applicable Law. (b) Environmental Laws. Each Owner shall comply with Environmental Laws in connection with its separate activities on the Transmission Route and Shared Facilities. Each Owner agrees to indemnify the other Owners and the Shared Facilities Manager against such Owner's violation of the Environmental Laws on the Transmission Route and Shared Facilities, including such violations by its agents or contractors. The foregoing indemnities shall not apply to the extent of any gross negligence or willful misconduct by the party being indemnified, or to any acts or omissions of the Shared Facilities Manager conducted with respect to the Shared Facilities in accordance with this Agreement and approved by the Owners Committee (it being understood and agreed that the Owners of applicable Segments of the Shared Facilities are jointly and severally liable for such acts or omissions of the Shared Facilities Manager). (c) Reserved. (d) Taxes. Subject to Section 4.2(j), each Owner shall pay, when due, all real and personal property taxes and assessments, general or special, levied against its facilities and/or operations subject to such Party's right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings the validity or applicability of any such taxes and assessments; provided that no such contest shall be permitted if it would expose the Shared Facilities to a risk of loss by forfeiture or otherwise. (e) Compliance with Law. Each Owner shall, at its sole cost and expense, promptly comply with all applicable statues, laws, ordinances, rules, regulations, orders and permits (collectively, "Laws") and with all covenants, conditions and restrictions in effect regulating the use of the Shared Facilities or any facilities owned by such Owner thereon until this Agreement is terminated; provided however, that such Owner shall have the right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings and in its own name the validity or applicability of any such Law; provided that no such contest shall be permitted if it would expose the Shared Facilities to a risk of loss by forfeiture or otherwise. (f) Conduct of Activities. Each Owner shall (i) conduct its operations and activities on the Transmission Route and the Shared Facilities in accordance with all Applicable Laws, Prudent Industry Practices and the Settlement Agreement, and (ii) to the extent necessary to avoid a material adverse effect with respect to the condition or operation of the Shared Facilities or an increase in insurance premiums with respect thereto, keep its facilities in good condition and repair, in good and efficient working order and in a safe condition. Neither any Owner nor the Shared Facilities Manager shall conduct its operations or activities, or use or permit the use of the Shared Facilities or any part thereof or its facilities in any manner that will cause physical damage the Shared Facilities or any part thereof, or cause an increase in insurance premiums with respect thereto and each Owner (and the Shared Facilities Manager, if not an Owner) shall be responsible for any such physical damage (but shall not incur any liability for any down-time resulting from any operations or activities conducted in accordance with Applicable Laws, Prudent Industry Practices, the Settlement Agreement and otherwise in accordance with this Agreement). Each Owner shall exercise reasonable efforts to coordinate with the other Owners in the timing and duration of maintenance to the transmission lines on the Shared Facilities and the other portions of the Owners' Projects (to the extent maintenance of such Projects would materially impair the use by the other Owners of the Shared Facilities or the transmission lines on such Shared Facilities); provided however, that if the Owners cannot agree to the timing and duration of such maintenance, an Owner shall have the unilateral right (without incurring any liability) to perform such maintenance provided that such maintenance time shall not exceed sixty (60) hours (in the aggregate) in any calendar year. (g) Each Owner shall operate and maintain its Project acting as a prudent operator and manager and otherwise (a) in accordance with the terms of its Project Interconnection Agreement, (b) in compliance with any other agreements, including those applicable to the provision of retail electricity service if applicable, that an Owner may have with the Participating TO, and (c) in compliance with the CAISO FERC Electric Tariff, including the rules, protocols, procedures, and standards attached thereto, as the same may be amended from time to time, in each case in a manner that will not have a material adverse effect on the ability of any other Project to remain interconnected with the Participating TO pursuant to its respective Project Interconnection Agreement. (h) Each Owner shall cause or authorize (as necessary) Transmission Provider to provide the Shared Facilities Manager notice of all amounts due to Transmission Provider for retail electricity (by amendment to its Project Interconnection Agreement or retail electricity contract or by other manner reasonably satisfactory to each other Owner), and provide evidence of such arrangement to each other Owner and the Shared Facilities Manager not later than December 31, 2016. (i) Each Owner shall designate the Shared Facilities Manager as a required recipient of any notices of breach, default or curtailment directives under the Owner's respective Project Interconnection Agreement and the CAISO Tariff and provide evidence of such arrangement to each other Owner and the Shared Facilities Manager not later than December 31, 2016. ARTICLE 8 TRANSFER OF INTERESTS; LIENS 8.1 Restrictions on Transfer No Owner shall sell, assign or otherwise transfer any of its ownership interest or other rights or interests in or to the Shared Facilities, or in, to or under this Agreement, without (i) assigning or transferring such Shared Facilities and Agreement rights and interests together to the same assignee(s), such that the Shared Facilities are not separated in ownership from the rights and interests under this Agreement (provided, however, that the Owners may apportion their interest in the Shared Facilities and their rights and obligations under this Agreement to multiple separate transferees that are successor owners of one or more of the Projects), and (ii) obtaining the prior written consent of all other Owners, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld by any such other Owners, except that such consent shall not be required for a sale, assignment or transfer by an Owner (a "Transferring Party") in the following circumstances: (a) the assignee or transferee is an entity with which the Transferring Party has consolidated or into which the Transferring Party has merged or which acquires by conveyance, transfer or lease all or substantially all of the assets of such Transferring Party and such purchaser, assignee, lessee or assignee shall have agreed in writing to assume all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement; or (b) the assignee or transferee owns (or will own upon the transfer) an appropriate equivalent ownership interest in the Project(s) owned by the Transferring Party which produce electricity transmitted over the lines supported by the Shared Facilities; or (c) a transfer in the nature of a lien, security interest or collateral assignment (each a "Lender's Lien") as security for a debt, equity or obligation to a third party (a "Lender"), or the foreclosure (or conveyance or assignment in lieu of foreclosure) of such Lender's Lien), provided that, in the case of foreclosure of a Lender's Lien, the requirements of (b) above are also met. The restrictions on transfer contained in this Section 8.1 shall not apply with respect to transfers of equity ownership in an Owner itself, or in connection with the transfer of assets, or equity interests in any entity, in either case owned by an owner, member, shareholder, or other person owning an equity interest (directly or indirectly) in an Owner. 8.2 Transfer Requirements Any sale, assignment or transfer made in accordance with Section 8.1 (i) shall relieve an Owner of any past obligation under this Agreement only to the extent consented to in writing by the other Owners, and (ii) shall relieve an Owner of any future obligation under this Agreement, only to the extent assumed by the transferee in writing. Except as permitted in Section 8.1, no Owner may transfer all or part of its rights to use the Shared Facilities separately from its ownership interest in the Shared Facilities. Any attempted or purported sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Shared Facilities or this Agreement made other than in accordance with this Article 8 either voluntarily or by operation of law shall be void and of no force or effect. 8.3 Obligations Regarding Liens Except for the existing encumbrances and encumbrances permitted pursuant to Section 8.1(c), the Parties hereto shall not, directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any lien on the Shared Facilities including taxes (other than for taxes not yet due), judgments, construction work, repair and restoration, or materials furnished. In the event of a violation of this Section which is not cured within thirty (30) calendar days after the offending Party receives notice of the recordation of such a lien, the other Parties shall be entitled to remove or cause the removal of such liens or encumbrances and to be reimbursed by the offending Party for all costs and expenses incurred in removing such liens or encumbrances. 8.4 Succession as "Owner" Any permitted purchaser, assignee or transferee (other than an assignee of a security interest pursuant to Section 8.1 prior to foreclosure thereon) shall be considered an "Owner" and a "Party" for purposes of this Agreement. 8.5 Lender Protection (a) Parties' Obligations. Each Party agrees to consent to financing documents as may reasonably be required by Lenders. As a precondition to exercising any remedies related to any alleged default by a Party under this Agreement, any other Party shall give notice of the default to each Lender at the same time it delivers notice of the default to the first Party, specifying in detail the alleged event of default and the required remedy. Each Lender shall have the same amount of time to cure the default as is given to the first Party and the same right to cure any default as the first Party. The cure period for each Lender shall begin to run at the end of the cure period given to Parties in this Agreement, but in no case shall the cure period for any Lender be less than thirty (30) calendar days after receipt of the notice of default. The Lender shall have the absolute right to substitute itself for the first Party and perform the duties of the first Party hereunder for purposes of curing such event of default. Each Party expressly consents to such substitution, agrees to accept such performance and authorizes the Lender (or its employees, agents, representatives or contractors) to enter upon the Transmission Route to complete such performance with all of the rights and privileges of the first Party hereunder. (b) Lender Obligations. Any Lender that does not directly hold an interest under this Agreement, or whose interest is held solely for security purposes, shall have no obligation or liability to any other Party for performance of a Party's obligations under this Agreement prior to the time the Lender directly holds an interest in this Agreement, or succeeds to absolute title to a Party's interest. A Lender shall be liable to perform obligations of a Party to the other Parties under this Agreement only for and during the period it directly holds such interest. Any assignment permitted under this Agreement shall release a Party or other assignor from obligations accruing after the date that liability is assumed by a transferee, but the assigning Party shall continue to be liable to the other Parties for all performance due by the assigning Party for matters that have accrued and are unsatisfied as of the date of the assignment. Further in the event that a Lender elects to (i) perform a Party's obligations under this Agreement, (ii) acquire any portion of a Party's right, title or interest in all or any of the Shared Facilities or (iii) enter into a new agreement as provided in Section 8.5(f), then such Lender shall not have any personal liability to a Party in connection therewith, and a non-defaulting Party's sole recourse in the event of default by such Lender shall be to execute against such Lender's interest in the Shared Facilities. Moreover, any Lender or other Person who acquires an interest in the Shared Facilities pursuant to foreclosure or an assignment in lieu of foreclosure shall not be liable to perform any obligations under the Agreement to the extent the same are incurred or accrue after such Lender or other Person no longer has ownership of such interest. (c) Lender's Right to Possession, Right to Acquire and Right to Assign. A Lender shall have the absolute right: (i) to assign its Lender's Lien; (ii) to enforce its Lender's Lien and acquire title to the applicable interest in the Shared Facilities by any lawful means; and (iii) to perform all obligations to be performed by a Party under this Agreement, or to cause a receiver to be appointed to do so. No Party's consent shall be required for any of the foregoing, and upon acquisition of an interest in the Shared Facilities by a Lender or any other third party who acquires the same from or on behalf of the Lender, a Party shall recognize the Lender or such other party (as the case may be) as the other Party's proper successor, and this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect. (d) Opportunity to Cure. Following acquisition of an interest in the Shared Facilities by the Lender as a result of either foreclosure or acceptance of an assignment in lieu of foreclosure, or by a purchaser at a foreclosure sale, this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect and the Lender or party acquiring title to such interest in the Shared Facilities shall, as promptly as reasonably possible, commence the cure of all defaults under this Agreement and thereafter diligently process such cure to completion; provided, however, that the Lender or party acquiring title to such interest in the Shared Facilities shall not be required to cure those defaults which are not reasonably susceptible of being cured or performed by such party ("Non-Curable Defaults"). Non-Curable Defaults shall be deemed waived by a Party upon completion of foreclosure proceedings or acquisition of the defaulting Party's interest in the Shared Facilities by such party. If a Lender is prohibited by any process or injunction issued by any court or by reason of any action of any court having jurisdiction over any bankruptcy or insolvency proceeding involving the defaulting Party from commencing or prosecuting the appropriate judicial or non-judicial proceedings, then any cure period for commencing such proceedings shall be extended for the period of such prohibition. (e) Termination. Neither the bankruptcy nor the insolvency of a Party shall be grounds for terminating this Agreement as long as all payments and all other monetary charges payable by the Party under this Agreement are paid by the Lender in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. (f) New Agreement. In the event that this Agreement is rejected or disaffirmed pursuant to bankruptcy law or any other law affecting creditors' rights, then, so long as a Lender has cured any such monetary event of default and is making commercially reasonable efforts to cure any such non-monetary event of default as provided herein, the non-defaulting Party(ies) shall, immediately upon request from such Lender received within ninety (90) calendar days after any such event, without demanding additional consideration therefor, enter into a shared use agreement with such Lender, which new shared use agreement shall (i) contain the same covenants, agreements, terms, provisions and limitations as this Agreement (except for any requirements that have been fulfilled by the Parties prior to such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance), and (ii) be for a term commencing on the date of such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance and continuing for the remaining term of this Agreement before giving effect to such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance. At the option of the Lender, the new shared use agreement may be executed by a designee of such Lender, with the Lender assuming the burdens and obligations of the defaulting Party thereunder. If more than one Lender makes a request for a new shared use agreement pursuant hereto, then the same shall be delivered to the Lender whose lien is senior in priority. (g) Lender Consent. Notwithstanding any provision of this Agreement to the contrary, (i) a Party shall not agree to a modification or amendment of this Agreement if the same could reasonably be expected to materially reduce the rights or remedies of a Lender or impair or reduce the security for a Lender's Lien, and (ii) a Party shall not accept a termination of this Agreement without the prior consent of each Lender. (h) Further Assurances. The Owners, the Shared Facilities Manager and the Owners Committee shall exercise commercially reasonable efforts, at their own cost and expense, to (i) cooperate in amending this Agreement from time to time to include any provision that may be reasonably requested by a Party or any Lender to implement the provisions contained in this Agreement or to preserve a Lender's Lien, (ii) execute any documents which may reasonably be required by a Party or a Lender to give effect to a provision of this Agreement and (iii) reasonable cooperate with the interconnection of any Project which is seeking to become an Interconnected Project, including as necessary temporarily curtailing or discontinuing deliveries of energy from any Interconnected Project for such reasonably minimal period of time as is necessary to perform the physical interconnection of a Project to the Shared Facilities. ARTICLE 13 MISCELLANEOUS 13.1 Several Obligations; Relationship of Parties Except to the extent otherwise expressly provided in Section 6.1(b), the duties, obligations and liabilities of the Owners under this Agreement are intended to be several and not joint or collective, and no Owner shall be jointly or severally liable for the acts, omissions or obligations of any other Owner. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be construed to create an association, joint venture, or partnership, or impose a partnership duty, obligation or liability, among the Owners. No Owner shall have a right or power to bind any other Owner without its express consent, except as expressly otherwise provided in this Agreement. 13.2 Regulatory Approvals and Assurances Each Party acknowledges and agrees that the use of the electrical transmission lines, conductors, insulators and other equipment for the circuits that will serve the Projects and are included in the Shared Facilities under this Agreement as well as the payments contemplated under Section 3.1 of this Agreement may constitute the provision of electric service under the Federal Power Act ("FPA") and therefore this Agreement will be filed with and accepted or approved by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("FERC") before the provisions of this Agreement providing for such use and payments become effective. The Owner that is the first Project to become an Interconnected Project under this Agreement will file this Agreement with the FERC requesting such approval or acceptance no less than sixty (60) days or more than one hundred twenty (120) days prior to the anticipated Interconnection Date for the second Project reasonably anticipated by the Shared Facilities Manager to become an Interconnected Project under this Agreement. 13.3 Removal of Shared Facilities from Service When all of the Owners direct the Shared Facilities Manager to permanently remove the Shared Facilities from service, the Shared Facilities Manager shall dispose of the Shared Facilities, or of such part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, being removed from service. After deducting all approved costs of disposing of the Shared Facilities, or of such part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, including the cost of removing all structures and disposing of the debris and meeting all requirements of Applicable Law, the Shared Facilities Manager shall distribute to each Owner its Proportionate Share of net proceeds from such disposition. If such costs of disposing of the Shared Facilities, or of part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, pursuant to this Section 13.3, exceed the amount of the proceeds from the disposition of the Shared Facilities or such part of the Shared Facilities, each Owner shall pay its Proportionate Share of excess costs related to the disposition of the Shared Facilities or of such part of the Shared Facilities, as the case may be, as such excess costs are incurred. 13.4 Withdrawal If an Owner shall elect to cease use of the Shared Facilities prior to the Interconnection Date for such Owner's Project, such Owner electing to cease use shall be released from this Agreement, provided it is not then in default under the Agreement. Following such release of an Owner from this Agreement, any other Owner or Owners may assume their Proportionate Share of the releasing Owner's ownership in and rights with respect to the Shared Facilities (including any insurance or condemnation proceeds with respect thereto). 13.5 Uncontrollable Forces No Owner shall be considered to be in default under this Agreement or in breach of this Agreement on account of any failure in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than obligations of such Owner to make any payments that are due and owing pursuant to this Agreement, if failure of such performance is due to the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event. "Force Majeure Event," as used herein, means any act or event that delays or prevents a Party from timely performing all or a portion of its obligations under this Agreement or from complying with all or a portion of the conditions under this Agreement if such act or event, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and is beyond the reasonable control of, and without the fault or negligence of, the Party relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance, or noncompliance. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, so long as the following events, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and are beyond the reasonable control of, and without the fault or negligence of, the Party relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance and noncompliance, Force Majeure Events may include: acts of God; actions of the elements such as heavy rains, floods, earthquakes, hurricanes, tornadoes, lightning, ice storms, landslides, mudslides, high winds of sufficient strength or duration to materially damage a Project or significantly impair its operation for a period of time longer than normally encountered by wind energy facilities under comparable circumstances; subsurface or other site conditions (including environmental contamination, archaeological or other protected cultural resources, and endangered species or protected habitats); explosion; fire; epidemic; sabotage; terrorism; transportation delays; unavailability of materials; an act of public enemy; war; blockade; civil insurrection; riot; civil disturbance or strike or other labor difficulty caused or suffered by a Party or any third Person beyond the reasonable control of such Party (or third Party) or its Affiliates (even if such difficulties could be resolved by conceding to the demands of a labor group); system emergencies affecting a Project; or any restraint or restriction imposed by Applicable Law or any directive from a Governmental Authority, which by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with Applicable Law a Party could not reasonably have been expected to avoid and to the extent which, by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with Applicable Law, has been unable to overcome (so long as the affected Party has not applied for or assisted such act by a Governmental Authority). Any Owner or Shared Facilities Manager rendered unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of a Force Majeure Event shall give notice of such Force Majeure Event promptly to each of the Owners and shall exercise due diligence to remove such inability and thereafter resume performance with all reasonable dispatch. 13.6 Run With the Land The Parties hereby agree that all of the covenants, consents and agreements contained in this Agreement touch and concern the Transmission Route and are expressly intended to, and shall, to the extent allowed by law, be covenants running with the land and shall be binding and a burden upon each Party's present or future estate in the Transmission Route and upon each of the Parties hereto from time to time, their respective successors and assigns as holders of an estate or interest in such real estate (including any Lender or other person acquiring title from any such person upon foreclosure or by deed in lieu of foreclosure), and shall benefit the Parties hereto from time to time and their respective successors and assigns. To the extent any of the provisions of this Agreement are not enforceable as covenants running with the land, they shall be enforceable as equitable servitudes. 13.7 Estoppel Certificates Upon the request of an Owner or any Lender, any other Owner, upon not less than ten (10) Business Days' notice, shall, if true, provide a certificate stating that (i) this Agreement is in full force and effect and has not been modified or amended (or if modified or amended, stating so), and (ii) to the actual knowledge of the certifying Owner, there are no defaults under this Agreement and no events that, with notice or the passage of time or both, could become a default (or if there are defaults, describing them in reasonable detail). The requesting Owner, and any purchaser, investor or Lender with respect to such Owner's portion of the Shared Facilities, shall be entitled to rely on the truthfulness of the statements made by the certifying Owner in such certificate. The failure of the nonrequesting Party to deliver any such certificate within such time shall be conclusive upon such nonrequesting Party that (a) this Agreement and the rights granted hereunder are in full force and effect and have not been modified and (b) there are no uncured defaults hereunder. 13.8 Partition Waiver The Owners agree that the Shared Facilities are not suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under Applicable Law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Shared Facilities. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Shared Facilities and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Article 8 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights. 13.9 Amendments This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties; provided however, that the Exhibits hereto and the definitions of "First Mover" and "Second Mover" as they apply to particular Segments may be amended from time to time by written agreement of the Owners of applicable Segments but only if such amendments or modifications could not reasonably be expected to adversely impact any other non-consenting Owners and could not reasonably be expected to materially reduce the rights or remedies of a Lender or impair or reduce the security for a Lender's Lien; provided further, that any Owner making an amendment or modification pursuant to this Section 13.9 that requires, or results in, a filing with, or notification of, FERC shall as promptly as practicable notify the other Owners and shall cooperate with the other Owners as reasonably necessary, in each case so that the other Owners will be able to comply with any applicable FERC regulations, including the filing of certificates of concurrence and tariff records. Following any amendment to the Exhibits hereto or the definitions of "First Mover" and "Second Mover" as they apply to particular Segments in accordance with the first proviso in the preceding sentence the Owners approving such amendment will promptly deliver a fully executed copy of such amendment to the other Parties hereto as well as a written description of the reason for the amendment and such Parties' certification that the amendment complies with the terms of this Section 13.9. 13.10 Further Assurances The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably requested by the Parties to implement this Agreement so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement. 13.11 Time of Essence Time is of the essence with regard to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. 13.12 Partial Invalidity Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall this Agreement continue for a term that is longer than the longest periods permitted by Applicable Law. 13.13 No Third Party Beneficiaries Except with respect to the rights of Indemnified Parties and the Shared Facilities Manager (if not a Party) as set forth herein, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto and their respective successors and permitted assigns, and shall not be construed as benefiting any person or entity that is not a Party. 13.14 Entire Agreement; Multiple Counterparts This Agreement, including the Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto (all of which are incorporated herein by this reference), contains the entire agreement between the Parties hereto in connection with any matter mentioned or contemplated herein, and all prior or contemporaneous proposals, agreements, understandings and representations, whether oral or written, are merged herein and superseded hereby.
